The paper deals with algorithms for computing minimum weight $k$-cuts in undirected graphs, which is a problem in graph theory and optimization. The paper uses techniques from linear programming, graph algorithms, and approximation algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
